# Group / Channel product alignment

## Principle

- Group and Channel are both **community workspaces** in one product family.
- Prefer **one mental model**: same layout, timeline, composer *shape*, tools sheet, theme, and mobile behavior.
- **Diverge only** where participation policy requires it (posting mode, membership semantics, reply rules)—not duplicate unrelated UIs.

## Before adding Channel-only or Group-only UI

Ask: is this difference **behavioral** (product) or **only permissions**?

- If **only permissions**: reuse the same workspace shell; branch with roles, `canPost`, `postingMode`, badges, placeholders, disabled composer + hint text.
- Do not build a separate “channel product” with unrelated patterns.

## Composer

- Same familiar surface: textarea + primary send, theme tokens (`theme-*`, `--accent`, `--border-soft`).
- Differences should be: enabled/disabled, placeholder, permission hint, mode badge—not a different interaction model.
- Extend shared primitives (e.g. `CommunityTextComposer`) rather than one-off channel styles.

## Tools & parity

- Linked capabilities, tools sheet, search, media, pins: **prefer parity** unless there is a clear product reason to omit on one side.

## References

- Group thread: `src/app/groups/[id]/page.tsx` (full chat; source of patterns).
- Channel thread: `src/app/channels/[id]/page.tsx` (should converge visually; policy-driven composer).
